- Test Cases: Users can create, view, update, and delete test cases. The system supports both manual test cases and AI-generated ones.
- AI Generation: A simple AI endpoint accepts a feature description and returns a generated test case (title, description, steps). The project includes a mock AI implementation so the feature works without external API keys.
- Reports: Users can store and retrieve execution reports for projects or test runs.
- Settings & Theme: Each user can store preferences (dark/light theme) which are saved in the database and exposed through the settings API.

Backend Architecture (summary)
- Built with Node.js + Express.
- RESTful API endpoints for authentication, projects, test cases, reports, settings, and AI-generation.
- Database-agnostic: supports MongoDB (Mongoose) by default, with a SQL fallback (Sequelize + SQLite) for environments where Mongo is unavailable.
- Middleware: central auth middleware validates JWTs and attaches the user to requests; an error handler ensures consistent error responses.
- Utilities: a logging helper and an AI mock generator make the backend self-contained and easy to run locally.

How the frontend interacts (brief)
- The completed frontend sends REST requests to endpoints such as:
  - `POST /api/auth/register` and `POST /api/auth/login` for authentication
  - `GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/projects` to manage projects
  - `GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/testcases` to manage test cases
  - `POST /api/generateTestCase` to generate AI-based test cases
  - `GET/POST /api/reports` to manage reports
  - `GET/POST /api/settings` to read/update theme preference
- Authenticated requests include a `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header returned by the login/register endpoints.

Developer notes
- The backend contains both `models/mongo` and `models/sql` directories. The runtime selects which to use via the `DB_TYPE` environment variable.
- A seed script is provided to populate dummy users, a demo project, a sample test case, and an initial report.
- The AI generator is a local mock that turns sentences in a feature description into ordered test steps; it is deterministic and requires no external API keys.

Running locally (quick)
1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and set `MONGO_URI` (or set `DB_TYPE=sql` to use SQLite).
2. From `Backend/` run `npm install` and then `npm run dev` to start the server.
3. Optionally run `npm run seed` to load sample data.

Why this matters
- InsightFlow reduces time spent writing manual test cases by bootstrapping them from natural language feature descriptions.
- The system is designed for beginners: code is commented and organized into controllers, routes, models, middleware, and utils for easy navigation and extension.

